      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Right Move on Oil</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Samuel M Greenhouse letter, commenting on September 25 article questioning Clinton administration's decision to tap Strategic Petroleum Reserve because of rising oil prices and tight supplies, says proper question is whether release of oil was essential, not whether it was political; backs administration's decision</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Some See Politics in Oil Release'' (news article, Sept. 25):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Some See Politics in Oil Release'' (news article, Sept. 25):</p>
        <p>We're entering the cold season. Tapping America's oil reserves might have been inadvisable some months ago, as Vice President Al Gore said then, but now is the right time. A frozen populace is not in America's security interest, and the release includes a replenishment provision.</p>
        <p>The administration's just-in-time response should prompt a ''thank Heaven for politics'' reaction instead of skepticism. The right question is whether the oil release was essential, not whether it was political.</p>
        <p>SAMUEL M. GREENHOUSE  Boca Raton, Fla., Sept. 25, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
